column5: Anyone know anything about this lake??????

This Lake is in the Chapleau Game Preserve- Looks like a decent size lake from the maps. Also wondering about Morin Lake. It appears the two lakes are conacted by a river. Any info. out there you can share. PM if you need to go that route. Thankyou
MORIN LAKE north and west of Chapleau--any of you guys ever been there or heard of the lake???????
Len , I sent you an email, but have not heard back from you . Maybe your email address changed ?? Going to Pickle Lake next week . Ogoki from Ohio (hunts Missaukee Co)

Solopaddler did a trip summary on here 3 years ago. I gave him a marked map from when I went there years ago. has become a great walleye lake, use to be just very nice pike. he portaged into morin and did very well there. http://www.ofncommunity.com/forums/i...howtopic=34926
